SIMPLE: evener
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Evener
<hw>E"ven*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which makes even.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In vehicles, a swinging crossbar, to the ends of
which other crossbars, or whiffletrees, are hung, to equalize the
draught when two or three horses are used abreast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Evenfall</ent>⟦br⟧
